<br>
u need to get unkos to militia so u can pull to newbie area and quad <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=franzia>Franzia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/1/01 9:08:07 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quading Steel Warriors in WFP??? HOW</span><hr size=1> what lvl did you start with these?<br>
<br>
(And I'm assuming you used CoF) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uxilet.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xilet</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/2/01 8:13:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quading Steel Warriors in WFP??? HOW</span><hr size=1> I spent 12 levels on them (35-47), they are all 35 with 1800 hp. There is Jakom whom I'm sure you all know by now. Also under the arena is 2 more (Trancil Clearpond and Monica Oakstone [may have screwed up the names a bit]). As a wizard in the levels there is not an aoe that does enough dmg to be able to tri kite these three, however with a good med kite (post 44) you can do all 3 with single blasts. However Dr00d aoe's at this level should be more than efficent enough to handle them /gesture<br>
Xilet 53 Wiz Bertoxx (Retired)<br>
Nogit 23 Enc <p><img src="http://xilet.hosting4less.com/hideme.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umcdermit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>mcdermit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/2/01 8:52:35 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quading Steel Warriors in WFP??? HOW</span><hr size=1> Hmm, xilet are you sure about your AoE information?<br>
<br>
Even against only 2 targets, CoF is as efficient as Conflag. With 1800 HP, each target will require 3 Conflags, so 2250 mana to kill all three. You can do the same thing casting Circle of Force 9 times, for only 1575 mana.<br>
<br>
Also, as far as I can tell, Druids don't get an AoE spell that outperforms CoF untill level 49, when they get Lightning Blast. They get Lighning Strike at 34 which has the same damage/mana ratio as CoF, but I've yet to meet a Druid that has as much mana as a Wizard of the same level.<br>
<br>
 <p>Zwobu &lt;Trade Foundation&gt; Innoruuk</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ueciterant.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eci Terant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/2/01 3:11:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quading Steel Warriors in WFP??? HOW</span><hr size=1> u guys forgot about vun winstone who i flux when he patrols around door in warrior guild (first pull) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ueciterant.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eci Terant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/2/01 3:12:31 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quading Steel Warriors in WFP??? HOW</span><hr size=1> o and i started them at 39, didnt use snare till 42 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uxilet.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xilet</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/2/01 10:54:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quading Steel Warriors in WFP??? HOW</span><hr size=1> I wasnt up to date with my druid aoes, however the diffrence is with CoF is it tends to be resisted too much to be effictive, also with jakom and the other two spawning seperately the time it takes to cast the needed CoF's (assuiming no resists/fizzels) is still longer than it would take to pull/snare all three, i found conflag was the easiest and least resisted method <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=franzia>Franzia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/5/01 6:53:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quading Steel Warriors in WFP??? HOW</span><hr size=1> Ok, I gave this a shot last night.  Jakom was taken, but the 2 under the arena were free, so I CoF'd them.  At 44, it took about 3 bubs of mana.  (I have 199 int, but not much extra mana gear).  With those 2, a little over a half blue bub per dual-kite.  Worked great; thanks for the info everyone (esp Eci Terant).<br>
<br>
Question:  HOW do you get Vun?  He never comes out of the building, and fluxing him as he's near the front door got the very, very red to me guildmaster biatch on me which I died to since I didn't realize who she was till too late. =)<br>
<br>
Thanks <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uelupiousebonshire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elupious Ebonshire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/1/01 1:41:41 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.cse.msu.edu/~westbri2/Elupious.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quading Steel Warriors in WFP??? HOW</span><hr size=1> You got the red bish on you? wow, i never got her all the times i pulled vun, of corse this was back in the day when we didnt dream about quad kiting yet....I think bonds of force still had a random duration like root<br>
 <p><BR>
<font color="#ff0000">Elupious Ebonshire<BR>
Evoker of the 55th Circle<BR>
Solusek Ro</font><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uellyri.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ellyri</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/2/01 9:56:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quading Steel Warriors in WFP??? HOW</span><hr size=1> I have found that the &quot;safe&quot; way to quad with BoF is to snare, then 5 AOE's, re-snare (until all are snared if you get resists), repeat...<br>
<br>
I have never had BoF drop using this pattern. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showMessage?topicID=27.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showMessage?topicID=14.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.emailToFriend?topicID=11.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.threadControl?topicID=11.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=11.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=11.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General Discussion<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm3">Trade Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm4">Rant Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm8">Mob Dropped Spells<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm10">Class Balance & Class Bugs<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm22">Out of Mana<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm27"